com/world/middle-east/saudi-arabia-arrests-over-15400-people-in-weekly-sweep-over-immigration-labour-and-border-violations/articleshow/132332837.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T20:12:28+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132332906,imgsize-959191.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan turns to army chief Asim Munir in battle against population growth]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132331938.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Asim Munir, the chief of the Pakistani army, has taken a notable role in a prominent committee tasked with tackling the pressing issue of population growth in the country. The committee aims to devise strategies to manage the rapidly increasing numbers. Federal Health Minister Syed Mustafa Kamal emphasized the critical nature of this initiative, in addition to talks on revising the National Finance Commission Award system.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-turns-to-army-chief-asim-munir-in-battle-against-population-growth/articleshow/132331938.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-turns-to-army-chief-asim-munir-in-battle-against-population-growth/articleshow/132331938.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T19:21:29+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132332025,imgsize-398204.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Award-winning UK crime writer Lynda La Plante faces driving ban over three speeding offences in 5 months]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132331272.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/award-winning-uk-crime-writer-lynda-la-plante-faces-driving-ban-over-three-speeding-offences-in-5-months/articleshow/132331272.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/award-winning-uk-crime-writer-lynda-la-plante-faces-driving-ban-over-three-speeding-offences-in-5-months/articleshow/132331272.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T18:48:54+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132331464,imgsize-891626.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[UK construction worker dies after falling from Birmingham children's hospital day after Prince Harry visit]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132333139.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/construction-worker-dies-after-falling-from-birmingham-childrens-hospital-day-after-prince-harry-visit/articleshow/132333139.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/construction-worker-dies-after-falling-from-birmingham-childrens-hospital-day-after-prince-harry-visit/articleshow/132333139.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T20:35:12+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132333154,imgsize-194582.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘I’ll play for India’: Popular US streamer IShowSpeed makes bold offer to help nation qualify for 2030 FIFA World Cup]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132331427.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[IShowSpeed joked that he would play for India’s national football team and help the country qualify for the 2030 World Cup. The YouTuber made the comments during a livestream while watching Spain vs Belgium. He said he could play as a winger, striker or attacking midfielder. While FIFA rules make the idea unrealistic, his support drew attention from football fans.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/ill-play-for-india-popular-us-streamer-ishowspeed-makes-bold-offer-to-help-nation-qualify-for-2030-fifa-world-cup/articleshow/132331427.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us-streamers/ill-play-for-india-popular-us-streamer-ishowspeed-makes-bold-offer-to-help-nation-qualify-for-2030-fifa-world-cup/articleshow/132331427.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T18:48:51+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Sumit Roy</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132331407,imgsize-925528.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Pakistan claims 88 militants killed in ongoing Balochistan crackdown]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132331157.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Pakistan's security forces have killed eighty-eight militants in Balochistan since July fifth.  Operation Shaban involves the army and paramilitary forces targeting militant hideouts.  This operation began after coordinated attacks rocked the province on July fifth.  Militants killed nine police personnel and abducted eighteen others at a checkpoint.  Violence also struck a local tribe, killing five and abducting eleven individuals.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-claims-88-militants-killed-in-ongoing-balochistan-crackdown/articleshow/132331157.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/pakistan/pakistan-claims-88-militants-killed-in-ongoing-balochistan-crackdown/articleshow/132331157.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T18:24:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132331169,imgsize-1431673.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Indian-origin tech leader killed by husband in Georgia over domestic dispute, wounded son runs to neighbors for help]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132330293.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a shocking domestic violence incident in Georgia, a man is charged after allegedly shooting his son and killing his wife. The injured son sought refuge with neighbors while Sheetal Wrzesien, the victim, a tech leader, was lying dead inside the house. The husband was arrested and charged with felony murder.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-origin-tech-leader-killed-by-husband-in-georgia-over-domestic-dispute-wounded-son-runs-to-neighbors-for-help/articleshow/132330293.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/indian-origin-tech-leader-killed-by-husband-in-georgia-over-domestic-dispute-wounded-son-runs-to-neighbors-for-help/articleshow/132330293.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-11T17:41:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132331431,imgsize-735605.cms"/></item></channel></rss>